@startuml
title Bunny Code Platform - Deployment Sequence Diagram

actor DevOps as "DevOps Engineer"
participant DockerCompose as "Docker Compose"
participant NginxContainer as "Nginx\nReverse Proxy"
participant AppContainer as "Backend API\n(Node.js/Express)"
participant MySQLContainer as "MySQL\nDatabase"
participant RedisContainer as "Redis\nCache"
participant SandboxContainer as "Code Execution\nSandbox"
participant S3 as "AWS S3"
participant CloudFront as "AWS CloudFront"
participant CloudWatch as "AWS CloudWatch"

== Deployment Initialization ==

DevOps -> DockerCompose: docker-compose up
activate DockerCompose

DockerCompose -> MySQLContainer: Create and start MySQL container
activate MySQLContainer
MySQLContainer -> MySQLContainer: Load schema.sql\nInitialize database
MySQLContainer --> DockerCompose: MySQL ready on port 3306

DockerCompose -> RedisContainer: Create and start Redis container
activate RedisContainer
RedisContainer -> RedisContainer: Load redis.conf\nInitialize cache
RedisContainer --> DockerCompose: Redis ready on port 6379

DockerCompose -> AppContainer: Create and start backend container
activate AppContainer
AppContainer -> AppContainer: Load environment variables\nfrom .env

AppContainer -> MySQLContainer: Test database connection
MySQLContainer --> AppContainer: Connection successful

AppContainer -> RedisContainer: Test cache connection
RedisContainer --> AppContainer: Connection successful

AppContainer -> S3: Verify S3 bucket access
activate S3
S3 --> AppContainer: Access granted

AppContainer -> CloudWatch: Initialize logging
activate CloudWatch
CloudWatch --> AppContainer: Logging configured

AppContainer -> AppContainer: Start Express server\nInitialize Socket.IO
AppContainer --> DockerCompose: Backend ready on port 3000

DockerCompose -> NginxContainer: Create and start Nginx container
activate NginxContainer
NginxContainer -> NginxContainer: Load nginx.conf\nLoad SSL certificates
NginxContainer -> AppContainer: Test upstream connection
AppContainer --> NginxContainer: Health check passed
NginxContainer --> DockerCompose: Nginx ready on ports 80/443

DockerCompose --> DevOps: All services deployed successfully
deactivate DockerCompose

== Runtime Service Interaction ==

DevOps -> NginxContainer: Request health check
NginxContainer -> AppContainer: Forward health check request
AppContainer -> MySQLContainer: Check DB connection
MySQLContainer --> AppContainer: DB healthy
AppContainer -> RedisContainer: Check cache connection
RedisContainer --> AppContainer: Cache healthy
AppContainer --> NginxContainer: 200 OK
NginxContainer --> DevOps: System healthy

== Code Execution Deployment ==

AppContainer -> DockerCompose: Request sandbox container
activate DockerCompose
DockerCompose -> SandboxContainer: Create isolated sandbox
activate SandboxContainer
SandboxContainer -> SandboxContainer: Load tool.js\nSet resource limits\n(CPU, Memory)
SandboxContainer --> AppContainer: Sandbox ready

AppContainer -> SandboxContainer: Deploy user code
SandboxContainer -> SandboxContainer: Execute code in isolation
SandboxContainer --> AppContainer: Execution result

AppContainer -> S3: Upload execution result
S3 --> AppContainer: Upload successful

AppContainer -> DockerCompose: Terminate sandbox
DockerCompose -> SandboxContainer: Stop and remove container
deactivate SandboxContainer
DockerCompose --> AppContainer: Sandbox cleaned up
deactivate DockerCompose

== CDN Content Deployment ==

AppContainer -> S3: Upload static assets\n(code files, images, recordings)
S3 --> AppContainer: Upload complete

S3 -> CloudFront: Sync content to CDN
activate CloudFront
CloudFront -> CloudFront: Distribute to edge locations
CloudFront --> S3: Content distributed

== Monitoring and Logging ==

AppContainer -> CloudWatch: Send application logs
AppContainer -> CloudWatch: Send metrics data
CloudWatch -> CloudWatch: Aggregate and store logs

MySQLContainer -> CloudWatch: Send database metrics
RedisContainer -> CloudWatch: Send cache metrics
NginxContainer -> CloudWatch: Send proxy metrics

DevOps -> CloudWatch: Query logs and metrics
CloudWatch --> DevOps: Dashboard and alerts

== Shutdown Sequence ==

DevOps -> DockerCompose: docker-compose down
activate DockerCompose

DockerCompose -> NginxContainer: Stop Nginx container
NginxContainer -> NginxContainer: Graceful shutdown
deactivate NginxContainer

DockerCompose -> AppContainer: Stop backend container
AppContainer -> MySQLContainer: Close DB connections
AppContainer -> RedisContainer: Close cache connections
AppContainer -> S3: Flush pending uploads
deactivate S3
AppContainer -> CloudWatch: Send final logs
deactivate CloudWatch
AppContainer -> AppContainer: Graceful shutdown
deactivate AppContainer

DockerCompose -> RedisContainer: Stop Redis container
deactivate RedisContainer

DockerCompose -> MySQLContainer: Stop MySQL container
MySQLContainer -> MySQLContainer: Flush data to disk
deactivate MySQLContainer

DockerCompose --> DevOps: All services stopped
deactivate DockerCompose

@enduml
